<! [CDATA[
 Mississippi State University Logo
Mississippi State University for Agriculture and Applied Science, commonly known as Mississippi State University, is a public land-grant research university adjacent to Starkville, Mississippi. It is classified among “R1: Doctoral Universities – Very High Research Activity” and has a total research and development budget of $239.4 million, the largest in Mississippi. The university was chartered as Mississippi Agricultural & Mechanical College on February 28, 1878 and admitted its first students in 1880.
You can download theMS Statelogo on full-version of the page.
